  "prompt": "Why wasn't John Williams hired to write the soundtrack to Rogue One?",
  "response": "John Williams was not hired to compose the soundtrack for \"Rogue One: A Star Wars Story\" primarily because of scheduling conflicts. At the time the film was in production, Williams was busy scoring \"Star Wars: The Force Awakens,\" which required considerable attention and effort. Consequently, the producers of \"Rogue One\" selected Michael Giacchino to compose the score. Giacchino was a fitting choice, given his experience and reputation in the industry, and his ability to create a musical score that complemented the established Star Wars musical universe while providing its own unique elements.",
